content:
Development environments are full-featured Salesforce environments that you use to develop and test existing or new features and custom applications. They include Developer Edition orgs, sandboxes, and scratch orgs.

Data Mask allows automating how frequently Data Mask runs and protects data with automation bypasses.

Select Who Has Sandbox Access for Production Orgs with 60 or More Public Groups provides access to a sandbox through a public group if the production org has 60 or more public groups.

Capture a Scratch Org’s Configuration with Scratch Org Snapshots captures a snapshot of a scratch org’s configuration so that it can be used to create scratch org replicas. 

Increase Sandbox Security with Inactive User Freezing freezes users in a Developer or Developer Pro sandbox within the first 60 days based on the time the user was created.

New User Permission: Manage Dev Sandboxes allows users to create, clone, refresh, and delete only Developer and Developer Pro sandboxes.

Test Data Cloud Features in a Sandbox (Beta) provides access to Data Cloud features in the same sandbox org for testing, staging, and training.
title: Salesforce Summer '24 Release Notes: Development Environments
